      "title": "Run the Application and API",
      "description": "## Run the Application and API\nNow that we've connected the Expenses Web Application to our Expenses API, let's run them both and take a look. \n\n1. From the top of the Run and Debug tab in Visual Studio Code, select 'Launch All' from the dropdown, then click the play icon. \n1. Your terminal will do some work, then provide a URL for the Expenses Web Application. Visit the Application and log in with the account you created in the 'Create an Application' Lab. \n\nWhile we've successfully wired our API up, it isn't yet secure. You can see this directly by appending the URL for your Expenses API with /reports. \n\nThe expense data is available publicly, without an Access Token. The next steps will change the API to require a properly-scoped Access Token to view.\n\nTo do this, weâ€™ll make use of an Express authentication middleware used to protect OAuth2 resources, which validates access tokens.  \n\nIt's time to make some adjustments to our Expenses API.\n\nWhen you've finished exploring the running applications, click next and we'll secure our API."
