      "file": "src/api/api/index.js",
      "description": "## Configure the API to use the Authentication Middleware\nNow, let's configure the API to use the middleware for all requests. \n\nHere, we'll addt the following code:\n\n``` jsx\n// ðŸ‘† public routes above ðŸ‘†\napp.use(auth());\n// ðŸ‘‡ private routes below ðŸ‘‡\n```\n\nNote the placement of this middleware between the â€œ/totalâ€ and â€œ/reportsâ€ endpoints. This is significant. \n\nJust like with web applications, some API endpoints are public. Endpoints above the middleware are open to the public while endpoints below require a valid oauth2 Access Token.  ",
